{
  "texts": [
    "It has been noted that the models that used datasets from MOOCs achieved a high predictive accuracy above 80%, except for one study Song et al (2020).",
    "On the other hand, it has been observed that some studies that have used datasets from LMSs platforms get a little higher prediction accuracy than what has been achieved using MOOCs datasets, the accuracy prediction through using of dataset from LMSs platforms range between 67.2% and 97%, with an average of 85.1% (see Figure 13).",
    "The LMS's average accuracy is a little less than that of MOOCs, which may be due to some studies that did not provide a numeric prediction accuracy of their models Prabowo et al (2021); Rahman et al (2022); Tao et al (2022).",
    "Another reason is that a considerable number of studies have low prediction accuracy compared to the studies using MOOCs datasets.",
    "For the datasets from other platforms, as shown in Figure 14, no pattern was found, and the prediction accuracy of the model ranged between 79.7% and 99%, with an average of about 90.97%."
  ]
}